SUMMARY:Keep Fit in Spring (6 sessions)
DESCRIPTION:Get your body moving and feeling good! This class combines gentle\, full-body exercises that boost your balance\, agility\, strength\, and posture—all while helping prevent pain\, stiffness\, and falls. With a mix of stretching\, light weights\, and mindful movement\, you’ll leave feeling stronger\, looser\, and more energized. It’s an hour of movement that’s as fun as it is good for you. \n\n\n\nTuesdays\, April 7 through May 12\, 10 to 11 a.m. (6 sessions)Public $90\, TBG Member $72  \n\n\n\nIf you are interested in a trial class\, please contact programsupport@torontobotanicalgarden.ca for more information. \n\n\n\nAbout Tena van AndelTena van Andel is a certified Level II 3-D Workout™ instructor who wants to keep all of us moving till we’re 102. She enjoys volunteering for the Toronto Master Gardeners and is busy rewilding a 19th-century rundown farmhouse\, fondly referred to as her ‘estate’. \n\n\n\nBecome a Member and SaveJoin the Toronto Botanical Garden (TBG) as a member to get a discount on this program\, upcoming events and classes\, and free parking. A TBG membership helps you deepen your knowledge and connection to the natural world\, become a part of a dynamic community of plant people\, and be inspired! Become a member! \n\n\n\nAdditional Program Information \n\n\n\n\nPlease review our Refund Policy and Terms of Agreement.\n\n\n\nFor more information on accessibility at the garden please review our Accessibility Features webpage. If you have any accessibility requirements during your program please email programsupport@torontobotanicalgarden.ca.\n\n\n\nTo learn more about the Toronto Botanical Garden and our programs\, please review our list of Frequently Asked Questions.
URL:https://torontobotanicalgarden.ca/event/keep-fit-in-spring-6-sessions/
LOCATION:Toronto Botanical Garden\, 777 Lawrence Ave E\, Toronto\, ON\, M3C 1P2\, Canada
CATEGORIES:Wellness
