SUMMARY:Beyond the Basics: Spring Succulent Arrangement Workshop
DESCRIPTION:Join us this Spring and go deeper into succulent arrangements! Take your succulent arranging skills to the next level in this workshop designed for enthusiasts ready to elevate their craft. Guided by an experienced succulent designer\, you’ll explore advanced techniques and expert tips to create show-stopping arrangements that thrive.\n \nThis hands-on workshop features the design and assembly of a stunning centerpiece arrangement in a large\, modern ceramic planter. Perfect for your dining table\, coffee table\, or entryway\, this statement piece will showcase your creativity and eye for design.\n \nWe’ll dive deeper into succulent styling principles\, including color harmony\, texture combinations\, and structural balance. You’ll also learn how to maintain larger arrangements and keep them vibrant year-round.\n \nAll materials are provided\, including premium succulent varieties\, specialty soil\, and a sleek ceramic planter. Bring your love for succulents and a willingness to experiment—you’ll leave with a centerpiece that’s truly a work of living art. Perfect for plant lovers ready to go beyond the basics!\n \nSaturday\, April 11\, 2 to 3 p.m.\nPublic $85\, TBG Members $80 (plus applicable taxes and fees).\n \nAbout Canadian Succulents\nCanadian Succulents is a small business that creates floral arrangements entirely from succulents and cacti. They not only arrange and design all of the creations but also grow all the plants that can be found in them as well. They operate out of a greenhouse just northeast of the city\, where they grow over 300 varieties of succulents and cacti. They grow and create these designs for wedding centrepieces and favors\, corporate events and gifting\, and hotel and office greenery.\nhttp://www.canadiansucculents.net/\n \nJoin Today!Join the Toronto Botanical Garden (TBG) as a member to get a discount on this program\, upcoming events and classes\, and free parking. A TBG membership helps you deepen your knowledge and connection to the natural world\, become a part of a dynamic community of plant people\, and be inspired! Become a member!\n\n\nAdditional Program Information \n\nPlease review our Refund Policy and Terms of Agreement.\nFor more information on accessibility at the garden please review our Accessibility Features webpage. If you have any accessibility requirements during your program please email programsupport@torontobotanicalgarden.ca.\nTo learn more about the Toronto Botanical Garden and our programs\, please review our list of Frequently Asked Questions.
URL:https://torontobotanicalgarden.ca/event/beyond-the-basics-spring-succulent-arrangement-workshop/
LOCATION:Toronto Botanical Garden\, 777 Lawrence Ave E\, Toronto\, ON\, M3C 1P2\, Canada
