SUMMARY:Book Launch: Trees and Shrubs of Mount Pleasant Cemetery by Janet Davis
DESCRIPTION:Celebrate the rich history of the Mount Pleasant Cemetery and join us for the launch of Janet Davis’ new book!\n \nPlease join us to mark the publication of the book Trees & Shrubs of Mount Pleasant Cemetery with author and TBG member Janet Davis. Published by Canada’s Firefly Books\, the book takes a four-season look at the woody plants in the 205-acre cemetery\, an accredited arboretum with one of the largest tree collections in Canada. This year marks the 150th anniversary of Mount Pleasant Cemetery and the 200th anniversary of Mount Pleasant Group\, which had its origins in Potter’s Field in what is now Toronto’s Yorkville. Janet will share images of some of her favourite trees and shrubs\, followed by a book sale and signing.\nFriday\, May\, 2 to 4 p.m.\nFree to attend. Please register beforehand so we know you’re coming! \n\nAbout Janet Davis\nJanet Davis is a freelance garden writer and photographer with a large image library. Over her 38-year career\, she has been a weekly gardening columnist for two of Toronto’s newspapers\, an online garden magazine editor\, and a contributor of photos and stories to numerous books and magazines\, including Trellis and the Toronto Botanical Garden’s website. Her new book\, Trees and Shrubs of Mount Pleasant Cemetery from publisher Firefly Books\, is the fruit of three decades of visits to the cemetery to observe the arboretum in all four seasons. She is currently writing a second book for Firefly titled A Garden Paintbox on colour in the garden. \n\nJoin Toronto Botanical Garden\nJoin the Toronto Botanical Garden (TBG) as a member to get a discount on this program\, upcoming events and classes\, and free parking. A TBG membership helps you deepen your knowledge and connection to the natural world\, become a part of a dynamic community of plant people\, and be inspired! Become a member !\nAdditional Program Information\n\n\n\nPlease review our Refund Policy and Terms of Agreement.\nFor more information on accessibility at the garden please review our Accessibility Features webpage. If you have any accessibility requirements during your program please email programsupport@torontobotanicalgarden.ca.\nTo learn more about the Toronto Botanical Garden and our programs\, please review our list of Frequently Asked Questions.
URL:https://torontobotanicalgarden.ca/event/book-launch-trees-and-shrubs-of-mount-pleasant-cemetery-by-janet-davis/
