SUMMARY:Fused Glass: Tree Motif Tealight Workshop
DESCRIPTION:Design and create a beautiful glass tea-light holder! Imagine a small grove of trees or a crop of mushrooms with a small tealight inside. Under the guidance of Fused Glass Artist Millean Kung\, you will be able to create two (2) Fused Glass Tealight Holders. During the class you will learn about fused glass\, compatibility\, how to cut glass\, safety\, and the firing of glass. All material and tools are included in this course and Beginners are welcome. Samples of these tealights can be seen in the Garden Shop.\n \nPlease note: the glass creations will be fused off-site and be available for pick up in 3 to 4 weeks following the class.\n \nThursday\, May 7\, 6:30 to 8:30 p.m.Public $115\, TBG Members $105 \n \nAbout Millean Kung\nBorn and raised in Toronto\, Millean discovered Pottery and Glass Art more than 10 years ago. Currently\, she is President of the Potter’s Studios in Scarborough and is involved in the Small Business Arts Mentorship Program at Glasstronomy Studios in Markham. Since retiring from education\, Millean has devoted her time to her Pottery and Glass Art. She is the sole proprietor of her business\, “1 in a Millean”\, and participates in a number of Arts and Crafts Shows. Millean also loves to garden and is a member and a volunteer at the Toronto Botanical Garden. To keep her schedule busy she enjoys cooking and baking.\nJoin Toronto Botanical Garden\nJoin the Toronto Botanical Garden (TBG) as a member to get a discount on this program\, upcoming events and classes\, and free parking. A TBG membership helps you deepen your knowledge and connection to the natural world\, become a part of a dynamic community of plant people\, and be inspired! Become a member!\n\n\nAdditional Program Information\n\nPlease review our Refund Policy and Terms of Agreement.\nFor more information on accessibility at the garden please review our Accessibility Features webpage. If you have any accessibility requirements during your program please email programsupport@torontobotnicalgarden.ca.\nTo learn more about the Toronto Botanical Garden and our programs\, please review our list of Frequently Asked Questions.
