SUMMARY:Mother's Day Succulent Workshop (Morning)
DESCRIPTION:Join us this Mother’s Day and create a one-of-a-kind succulent!\n\n\nCelebrate Mother’s Day with an afternoon of creativity\, connection\, and indulgence at our special succulent arranging workshop. Treat yourself and the moms in your life to a unique experience that blends nature\, artistry\, and a touch of sweetness. \nGuided by an expert succulent designer\, you’ll learn tips for succulent care and styling before diving into the hands-on creation of a vibrant succulent arrangement. \nDesign your masterpiece in a charming hand-made heart-shaped planter\, perfect for adding a splash of color and personality to any space. All materials\, including premium succulents\, specialty soil\, and care cards\, are provided—so you can focus on making memories and crafting a one-of-a-kind piece. \nSnack on some tea and beautiful floral cookies and leave with a beautiful creation and cherished moments to treasure. \nSunday\, May 10 from 10 to 11 a.m. \nPublic $80\, TBG Members $75 (plus applicable taxes and fees). \nAbout Canadian Succulents \nCanadian Succulents is a small business that creates floral arrangements using entirely succulents and cacti plants. They not only arrange and design all of the creations but also grow all the plants that can be found in them as well. They operate out of a greenhouse just north east of the city\, where they grow over 300 varieties of succulents and cacti. They grow and create these designs for wedding centrepieces and favors\, corporate events and gifting\, and hotel and office greenery. \nhttp://www.canadiansucculents.net/ \nJoin Toronto Botanical Garden \nJoin the Toronto Botanical Garden (TBG) as a member to get a discount on this program\, upcoming events and classes\, and free parking. A TBG membership helps you deepen your knowledge and connection to the natural world\, become a part of a dynamic community of plant people\, and be inspired! Become a member! \nAdditional Program Information \n\nPlease review our Refund Policy and Terms of Agreement.\nFor more information on accessibility at the garden please review our Accessibility Features webpage. If you have any accessibility requirements during your program please email programsupport@torontobotanicalgarden.ca.\nTo learn more about the Toronto Botanical Garden and our programs\, please review our list of Frequently Asked Questions.
URL:https://torontobotanicalgarden.ca/event/mothers-day-succulent-workshop-morning-2/
LOCATION:Toronto Botanical Garden\, 777 Lawrence Ave E\, Toronto\, ON\, M3C 1P2\, Canada
CATEGORIES:Art,Mothers Day
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://torontobotanicalgarden.ca/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cb6a00732472e35e693d07ea23c0d9da.jpg
END:VEVENT
