SUMMARY:Floral Design Program: Foliage Manipulation
DESCRIPTION:Join us and learn the art of manipulating foliage! Manipulating foliage is one of the most important techniques in floral design and indispensable in modern\, contemporary\, and abstract work. Manipulating foliage in a design can create rhythm\, interest\, impact\, and abstraction. In this hands-on course learn how to use techniques like rolling\, plaiting\, braiding\, and boondoggling on leaves such as aspidistra\, flax\, and palm.\n \nAll foliage plant material is provided for this class. A $100 course fee for the foliage material will be paid directly to your instructor. Information on how to submit payment for these materials will be provided prior to the start of your first class.\n \nLearn more about our Certificate in Floral Design\nPrerequisites: Classic Design Fundamentals 1 & 2\n \nMondays\, June 1 through 22\, 6 to 9 p.m.Public $240\, Members $190 \n \nRegistration Deadline: Thursday\, May 28 at 5 p.m.\n\n\nAbout Lil Taggart\nLil Taggart is an experienced and creative designer and instructor in Floral Arts. She is also an accredited Floral Design Judge and has competed on an international level as well as domestically. She serves on the board of Canada Blooms\, co-chairs the staging for the Toronto Flower Show\, is past president of the Georgetown Horticultural society and is a member of The Garden Club of Toronto. \nJoin Toronto Botanical Garden\nJoin the Toronto Botanical Garden (TBG) as a member to get a discount on this program\, upcoming events and classes\, and free parking. A TBG membership helps you deepen your knowledge and connection to the natural world\, become a part of a dynamic community of plant people\, and be inspired! Become a member! \nAdditional Program Information\n\nPlease review our Refund Policy and Terms of Agreement.\nFor more information on accessibility at the garden please review our Accessibility Features webpage. If you have any accessibility requirements during your program please email programsupport@torontobotanicalgarden.ca.\nTo learn more about the Toronto Botanical Garden and our programs\, please review our list of Frequently Asked Questions.
URL:https://torontobotanicalgarden.ca/event/floral-design-program-foliage-manipulation-3/
LOCATION:Toronto Botanical Garden\, 777 Lawrence Ave E\, Toronto\, ON\, M3C 1P2\, Canada
